Module org.nasdanika.emf
Package org.nasdanika.emf

Interface Palette

  • All Superinterfaces:
    EReferencePredicate
    public interface Palette
extends EReferencePredicate
    Palettes are used for grouping of EObjects, e.g. child candidates for containment references. Palettes allow to manage reference children in groups and also to have pre-configured children, e.g. objects with pre-populated structural features. Palette extends EReferencePredicate so it can be used by control flow (if, for, ...) and reference model elements to filter candidates for a reference.
    Author:
    Pavel

      • add

        default void add​(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EClass eClass,
                 EReferencePredicate predicate)
        Adds a contributor which instantiates given EClass and uses EClass name and EPackage namespace URI as ID. The contributor also implements EReferencePredicate delegating to the predicate parameter. It allows to filter palette elements based on the container and containing reference. Also adds predicates checking that a candidate is instance of one of provided EClass'es.

        eClass -
